# Fixture FM1: Leading digit in local part of prefixed name.
#
# Hypothesis: Parsers that follow XML NCName rules (which forbid a leading
# digit) will reject `ex:123` as invalid. Turtle §6.3 grammar explicitly
# allows [0-9] at the start of PN_LOCAL — this is a deliberate deviation
# from XML namespace conventions.
#
# Expected: parse succeeds; the triple subject is <http://example/123>.
# Divergence signal: AcceptRejectSplit between a conformant parser and one
# that applies XML NCName constraints to PN_LOCAL.
#
# Spec: Turtle §6.3 PN_LOCAL ::= (PN_CHARS_U | ':' | [0-9] | PLX) ...
# Errata: w3c/rdf-tests issue #90.

@prefix ex: <http://example/> .

ex:123      ex:p   ex:o .
ex:0start   ex:p   ex:o .
ex:9end     ex:p   ex:o .
